{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"1602","heading":"Definitions","label":"1602 Definitions","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/ch21","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","Effective DateSection applicable to all civil actions covered under this chapter commenced on or after , including any in which the harm or harmful conduct occurred before such date, see , set out as a note under .Aug. 13, 1998section 8 of Pub. L. 105–230section 1601 of this title"],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"Biomaterials supplier","label":"1 Biomaterials supplier","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":"In general","label":"A In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “biomaterials supplier” means an entity that directly or indirectly supplies a component part or raw material for use in the manufacture of an implant.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":"Persons included","label":"B Persons included","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/1/B/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F1%2FB%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"has submitted master files to the Secretary for purposes of premarket approval of a medical device; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/1/B/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F1%2FB%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"licenses a biomaterials supplier to produce component parts or raw materials.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Claimant","label":"2 Claimant","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":"In general","label":"A In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “claimant” means any person who brings a civil action, or on whose behalf a civil action is brought, arising from harm allegedly caused directly or indirectly by an implant, including a person other than the individual into whose body, or in contact with whose blood or tissue, the implant is placed, who claims to have suffered harm as a result of the implant.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":"Action brought on behalf of an estate","label":"B Action brought on behalf of an estate","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"With respect to an action brought on behalf of or through the estate of a deceased individual into whose body, or in contact with whose blood or tissue the implant was placed, such term includes the decedent that is the subject of the action.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":"Action brought on behalf of a minor or incompetent","label":"C Action brought on behalf of a minor or incompetent","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/2/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F2%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"With respect to an action brought on behalf of or through a minor or incompetent, such term includes the parent or guardian of the minor or incompetent.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":"Exclusions","label":"D Exclusions","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/2/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F2%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/2/D/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/2/D","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F2%2FD%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"I","heading":null,"label":"I","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/2/D/i/I","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/2/D/i","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F2%2FD%2Fi%2FI","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the sale or use of an implant is incidental to such services; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"II","heading":null,"label":"II","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/2/D/i/II","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/2/D/i","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F2%2FD%2Fi%2FII","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the essence of the professional health care services provided is the furnishing of judgment, skill, or services;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/2/D/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/2/D","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F2%2FD%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a person acting in the capacity of a manufacturer, seller, or biomaterials supplier; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iii","heading":null,"label":"iii","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/2/D/iii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/2/D","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F2%2FD%2Fiii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"I","heading":null,"label":"I","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/2/D/iii/I","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/2/D/iii","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F2%2FD%2Fiii%2FI","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"neither the exclusion provided by this clause nor any other provision of this chapter may be construed as a finding that silicone gel (or any other form of silicone) may or may not cause harm; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"II","heading":null,"label":"II","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/2/D/iii/II","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/2/D/iii","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F2%2FD%2Fiii%2FII","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"item","nativeType":"item","number":"aa","heading":null,"label":"aa","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/2/D/iii/II/aa","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/2/D/iii/II","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F2%2FD%2Fiii%2FII%2Faa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"be disclosed to a jury in any civil action or other proceeding; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"item","nativeType":"item","number":"bb","heading":null,"label":"bb","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/2/D/iii/II/bb","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/2/D/iii/II","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F2%2FD%2Fiii%2FII%2Fbb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"except as necessary to establish the applicability of this chapter, otherwise be presented in any civil action or other proceeding.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":"Component part","label":"3 Component part","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":"In general","label":"A In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/3/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F3%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “component part” means a manufactured piece of an implant.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":"Certain components","label":"B Certain components","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/3/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F3%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/3/B/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/3/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F3%2FB%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"has significant non-implant applications; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/3/B/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/3/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F3%2FB%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"alone, has no implant value or purpose, but when combined with other component parts and materials, constitutes an implant.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":"Harm","label":"4 Harm","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":"In general","label":"A In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/4/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F4%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/4/A/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/4/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F4%2FA%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"any injury to or damage suffered by an individual;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/4/A/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/4/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F4%2FA%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"any illness, disease, or death of that individual resulting from that injury or damage; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iii","heading":null,"label":"iii","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/4/A/iii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/4/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F4%2FA%2Fiii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"any loss to that individual or any other individual resulting from that injury or damage.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":"Exclusion","label":"B Exclusion","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/4/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F4%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term does not include any commercial loss or loss of or damage to an implant.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":"Implant","label":"5 Implant","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/5/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/5","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F5%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/5/A/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/5/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F5%2FA%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to be placed into a surgically or naturally formed or existing cavity of the body for a period of at least 30 days; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/5/A/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/5/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F5%2FA%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to remain in contact with bodily fluids or internal human tissue through a surgically produced opening for a period of less than 30 days; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/5/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/5","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F5%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"suture materials used in implant procedures.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"6","heading":"Manufacturer","label":"6 Manufacturer","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/6","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F6","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/6/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/6","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F6%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"is engaged in the manufacture, preparation, propagation, compounding, or processing (as defined in ) of the implant; andsection 360(a)(1) of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/6/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/6","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F6%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/6/B/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/6/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F6%2FB%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to register with the Secretary pursuant to and the regulations issued under such section; andsection 360 of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/6/B/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/6/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F6%2FB%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to include the implant on a list of devices filed with the Secretary pursuant to and the regulations issued under such section.section 360(j) of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"7","heading":"Medical device","label":"7 Medical device","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/7","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F7","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “medical device” means a device, as defined in , and includes any device component of any combination product as that term is used in .section 321(h) of this titlesection 353(g) of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"8","heading":"Raw material","label":"8 Raw material","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/8","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F8","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/8/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/8","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F8%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"has a generic use; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/8/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/8","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F8%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"may be used in an application other than an implant.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"9","heading":"Secretary","label":"9 Secretary","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/9","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F9","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “Secretary” means the Secretary of Health and Human Services.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"10","heading":"Seller","label":"10 Seller","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/10","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F10","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":"In general","label":"A In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/10/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/10","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F10%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “seller” means a person who, in the course of a business conducted for that purpose, sells, distributes, leases, packages, labels, or otherwise places an implant in the stream of commerce.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":"Exclusions","label":"B Exclusions","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/10/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/10","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F10%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/10/B/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/10/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F10%2FB%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a seller or lessor of real property;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/10/B/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/10/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F10%2FB%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"I","heading":null,"label":"I","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/10/B/ii/I","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/10/B/ii","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F10%2FB%2Fii%2FI","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the sale or use of the implant is incidental to such services; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"II","heading":null,"label":"II","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/10/B/ii/II","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/10/B/ii","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F10%2FB%2Fii%2FII","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the essence of the professional health care services provided is the furnishing of judgment, skill, or services; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iii","heading":null,"label":"iii","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/10/B/iii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1602/10/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1602%2F10%2FB%2Fiii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"any person who acts in only a financial capacity with respect to the sale of an implant.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}]}
